<main>
  <div class="updated">
    <strong>Last updated:</strong> March 9, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp;
    <strong>Effective:</strong> March 9, 2026
  </div>

  <p>
    Welcome to DishDrop ("we," "us," or "our"). This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
    disclose, and safeguard your information when you use the DishDrop mobile application. Please
    read it carefully. By using DishDrop you agree to the practices described below.
  </p>

  <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>We collect the following categories of information:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Account information:</strong> email address, display name, and optional profile photo when you register.</li>
    <li><strong>Profile information:</strong> username (handle), bio, and creator status that you choose to provide.</li>
    <li><strong>User-generated content:</strong> recipes, photos, videos, comments, and collections you create or upload.</li>
    <li><strong>Social interactions:</strong> likes, follows, favorites, and notifications generated by your activity.</li>
    <li><strong>Device information:</strong> push notification token, device type, and operating system version for notification delivery.</li>
    <li><strong>Usage data:</strong> in-app interactions such as recipe views, search queries, and session activity collected to improve the service.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>2. Camera, Microphone &amp; Photo Library</h2>
  <p>
    DishDrop requests access to your device's camera, microphone, and photo library solely to
    support core app features:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Camera &amp; Microphone:</strong> used to capture recipe photos, record cooking videos, and enable live cooking streams via Agora.</li>
    <li><strong>Photo Library (read):</strong> used to select existing photos and videos when creating or editing a recipe post.</li>
    <li><strong>Photo Library (write):</strong> used to save recipe media to your device when you choose to do so.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    We do not access your camera, microphone, or photo library in the background. Media you upload
    is stored securely in Firebase Storage and is only accessible according to your post's
    visibility settings (public or private).
  </p>

  <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>To create and manage your account.</li>
    <li>To display your recipes and profile to other users.</li>
    <li>To power social features (follows, likes, comments, notifications).</li>
    <li>To generate AI-powered recipe suggestions and grocery lists using Anthropic's Claude API.</li>
    <li>To enable live cooking streams using Agora RTC.</li>
    <li>To deliver push notifications about activity on your content.</li>
    <li>To display advertisements through Google AdMob.</li>
    <li>To detect, prevent, and address technical issues and policy violations.</li>
    <li>To improve the app's functionality and user experience.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>4. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>DishDrop integrates the following third-party services, each with their own privacy practices:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Google Firebase</strong> (Authentication, Firestore, Storage) —
      <a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Google AdMob</strong> (in-app advertising) —
      <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Agora</strong> (live video streaming) —
      <a href="https://www.agora.io/en/privacy-policy/" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Anthropic</strong> (AI recipe generation via Claude API) —
      <a href="https://www.anthropic.com/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Expo / EAS</strong> (app delivery and push notifications) —
      <a href="https://expo.dev/privacy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>5. Data Sharing &amp; Disclosure</h2>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information. We may share information in the following circumstances:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>With other users:</strong> public recipes, profile info, and comments are visible to all DishDrop users.</li>
    <li><strong>With service providers:</strong> we share data with the third-party services listed above to operate the app.</li>
    <li><strong>For legal reasons:</strong> if required by law, court order, or to protect the rights and safety of users or the public.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    We retain your account data and content for as long as your account is active. If you delete
    your account, we will remove your personal information and content from our servers within
    30 days, except where retention is required by law or to resolve disputes.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Security</h2>
  <p>
    We use industry-standard security measures including Firebase Authentication, Firestore
    security rules, and encrypted data transmission (HTTPS/TLS) to protect your information.
    However, no method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure and we cannot guarantee
    absolute security.
  </p>

  <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    DishDrop is not directed to children under 13 years of age. We do not knowingly collect
    personal information from children under 13. If you believe a child under 13 has provided us
    with personal information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Your Rights &amp; Choices</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Access &amp; correction:</strong> you can view and edit your profile information at any time within the app.</li>
    <li><strong>Delete account:</strong> you can request account deletion by contacting us at the email below.</li>
    <li><strong>Push notifications:</strong> you can disable push notifications in your device's settings at any time.</li>
    <li><strong>Ad personalization:</strong> you can opt out of personalized ads through your device's advertising settings.</li>
    <li><strong>Camera / Photo permissions:</strong> you can revoke these permissions at any time in your device's settings.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of material changes
    by updating the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. Your continued use of DishDrop
    after changes are posted constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.
  </p>

